precis:
SCHEDULE NO. 737 to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS - which defines
"expiration date" as being the last day upon which a drug maintains its
labelled potency, purity and physical characteristics, and requires that
such a date be inscribed on the packaging of all drug products.
